<task id="022" project="email-communication-solution-r3">
  <metadata>
    <title>SendEmailDialog wrapper — rewrite existing dialog as canonical wrapper around engine</title>
    <phase>Wave 1 — Engine + Wrappers + Sub-Components</phase>
    <status>not-started</status>
    <estimated-hours>4</estimated-hours>
    <dependencies>005, 020</dependencies>
    <blocks>050, 051</blocks>
    <tags>react, frontend, communication, refactoring</tags>
    <rigor-hint>FULL</rigor-hint>
    <rigor-reason>Rewrites EXISTING component (`src/.../SendEmailDialog/SendEmailDialog.tsx`) — touching production code consumed by LegalWorkspace/.../FilePreviewDialog.tsx. Migration risk: ISendEmailDialogProps shape change (`onSend` → `onSent` per FR-14); ADR-021 a11y + ADR-019 error contract carry through. FULL is appropriate.</rigor-reason>
    <parallel-group>E</parallel-group>
    <parallel-safe>true</parallel-safe>
    <fr-refs>FR-03</fr-refs>
  </metadata>

  <prompt>
    Rewrite the EXISTING `src/client/shared/Spaarke.UI.Components/src/components/SendEmailDialog/SendEmailDialog.tsx` as a canonical thin wrapper around `<EmailComposer mount='dialog' />`. Locks `mount='dialog'`. Internal Dialog chrome via Fluent v9 `<Dialog>` from the wrapper (engine's ActionsRegion handles footer actions). This task makes the existing public API path (`@spaarke/ui-components` exports `SendEmailDialog`) point at the canonical impl — consumers (FilePreviewDialog in Wave 3) don't need any code change beyond removing inline `fetch`.

    Props (FR-03):
    - `open: boolean`
    - `onClose: () => void`
    - `initialTo?: IRecipient[] | string`
    - `initialSubject?: string`
    - `initialBody?: string`
    - `associations?: IComposerAssociation[]`
    - `attachmentSources?: IComposerAttachmentSource[]` — defaults to `[{ kind: 'local' }, { kind: 'spe' }]` if not specified
    - `authenticatedFetch: typeof fetch` — injected (NFR-02)
    - `onSent?: (communicationId: string) => void` — fired on successful send; wrapper calls `onClose()` after
    - `onError?: (err: SendCommunicationError) => void` — fired on send failure
    - `defaultBodyFormat?: 'html' | 'plaintext'` — defaults to 'html'

    Implementation:
    - `<Dialog open={open} onOpenChange={(e, data) => !data.open && onClose()}>`
    - Inside: `<DialogSurface><EmailComposer mount='dialog' mode='compose' ref={composerRef} ... /></DialogSurface>`
    - Internal `composerRef = useRef<IEmailComposerHandle>()` — wrapper owns the send orchestration via the engine's ActionsRegion buttons (which call into the imperative handle)
    - On send success → `onSent(communicationId); onClose();`
    - On send failure → `onError(err)` (does NOT auto-close — user can retry)

    NOTE: This rewrites the EXISTING file. Old impl had `onSend` callback (different contract). The migration path is:
    1. This task replaces the file body with the canonical wrapper.
    2. ISendEmailDialogProps is updated to the new shape (`open`/`onClose`/`onSent`/`onError`).
    3. Wave 3 task 051 migrates `LegalWorkspace/FilePreviewDialog.tsx` to the new prop API.
    4. Any other consumers found by grep at Wave 3 start get migrated in same PR.

    Update barrel: `EmailComposer/index.ts` re-exports `SendEmailDialog` from the wrappers dir; legacy import path `import { SendEmailDialog } from '@spaarke/ui-components'` continues to resolve (via shared lib `src/index.ts`).
  </prompt>

  <role>
    Senior React developer comfortable with rewriting a shipped component while preserving (or upgrading) its public-export path.
  </role>

  <goal>
    Existing `SendEmailDialog/SendEmailDialog.tsx` rewritten as canonical wrapper. Locks `mount='dialog'`. New props API per FR-03. Old `onSend` callback REMOVED (Wave 3 migrates consumers). Re-export from `EmailComposer/wrappers/SendEmailDialog.tsx` is the canonical location; `SendEmailDialog/SendEmailDialog.tsx` becomes a thin re-export from the canonical location (to preserve existing import paths).
  </goal>

  <context>
    <background>
      Per FR-03 + Owner Clarifications: keep the 3 thin wrappers. Existing `SendEmailDialog` consumed by `LegalWorkspace/.../FilePreviewDialog.tsx` (per spec + assessment). Rewriting it lets us migrate the LegalWorkspace consumer in Wave 3 task 051 with minimal-footprint changes (just the prop API rename).

      Two physical files:
      - **Canonical**: `EmailComposer/wrappers/SendEmailDialog.tsx` — new home; thin wrapper around engine.
      - **Legacy path preserved**: `SendEmailDialog/SendEmailDialog.tsx` — becomes `export { SendEmailDialog } from '../EmailComposer/wrappers/SendEmailDialog';` so existing `import { SendEmailDialog } from '@spaarke/ui-components'` doesn't break during migration.

      Wave 0 task 005 added `SendCommunicationError` to `communicationApi.ts` — engine uses it; wrapper surfaces it via `onError`.
    </background>
    <relevant-files>
      <file>src/client/shared/Spaarke.UI.Components/src/components/EmailComposer/wrappers/SendEmailDialog.tsx (NEW — canonical)</file>
      <file>src/client/shared/Spaarke.UI.Components/src/components/SendEmailDialog/SendEmailDialog.tsx (REWRITE — thin re-export from canonical)</file>
      <file>src/client/shared/Spaarke.UI.Components/src/components/SendEmailDialog/index.ts (UPDATE — export canonical type)</file>
      <file>src/client/shared/Spaarke.UI.Components/src/components/EmailComposer/index.ts (UPDATE — export SendEmailDialog + ISendEmailDialogProps)</file>
      <file>src/client/shared/Spaarke.UI.Components/src/services/communicationApi.ts (READ — SendCommunicationError signature)</file>
    </relevant-files>
  </context>

  <constraints>
    <constraint source="ADR-019">`onError` receives typed `SendCommunicationError` — never raw `Error` or `{success, warning}`</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-021">Fluent v9 only — `Dialog`, `DialogSurface`, `DialogBody`</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-028">No `@spaarke/auth` import — `authenticatedFetch` injected (NFR-02)</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-033">Thin wrapper — engine carries the email logic</constraint>
    <constraint source="NFR-03">Locks `mount='dialog'` — wrapper sets it; host cannot override</constraint>
    <constraint source="NFR-06">Uniform error contract — `onError` always gets `SendCommunicationError`</constraint>
    <constraint source="project">Preserve existing import path `import { SendEmailDialog } from '@spaarke/ui-components'` via legacy file re-export</constraint>
    <constraint source="project">`onSend` callback (legacy) REMOVED — Wave 3 migrates consumers to `onSent`</constraint>
  </constraints>

